reviews.review_text: Ordered veg biryani which, when compared to the price on the menu was 180 and got a bill of 220rs which in and around vasco is high the quantity is good but quality not worthy.

We were the last customers for the noon. My 7yo daughter & I reached almost at 4pm, but Prashant the Manager welcomed us with a smile. He politely requested to order the food in one go, as the Chef was about to go. We ordered Palak Paneer, Tandoori Roti, & Rice. I asked Prashant what's for desserts & he recommended Punjabi Kheer. The food was delicious & my daughter enjoyed every bit of it. Prashant was patient enough to wait for us & made sure my daughter took her time to finish the lunch. It was his kind gesture which added flavors to the delicacies.

I had the misfortune to taste the food made by Punjabi dhaba. I had ordered chicken based side dishes from them . The food was horrible and inedible to say the least.  It was very hard and we had to throw away the food after trying to chew a few  pieces . There was some hard pieces in both the  dishes and we got worried as to what was delivered to us .
